  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Slavery in Brazil - The voice of those excluded</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over the past 20 years, almost 50,000 people were freed from slave labor on farms and coal plants across Brazil. Reporter Brasil is recognized as the most important source of information on slave labor in Brazil, both within and outside the country. Its reports, research and educational methodology are used by government, businesses and civil society as instruments of daily work. With this project, we want to produce 100 reports and analysis on cases and complaints of slavery in 2015.</narrative>
  </description>
